## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Rukaya AI Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Vercel Analytics component to the root layout

### Implementation Details

1. **Package Installation**: The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already present in package.json, so no additional installation was required.

2. **Framework Detection**: Identified the project as using Next.js 16.2.1 with the App Router architecture.

3. **Analytics Integration**: 
   - Imported the `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/next`
   - Added the component to the root layout at `frontend/src/app/layout.tsx`
   - Placed the `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the children content
   - This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router setup

4. **Verification**:
   - Successfully built the project with `npm run build`
   - All TypeScript compilation passed
   - No new linting errors were introduced by the changes
   - The build completed successfully with all routes properly generated

### Technical Notes

- The Analytics component was added to the root layout, which ensures it will be present on all pages of the application
- The component is placed at the end of the body tag to avoid blocking page rendering
- Following Next.js App Router best practices, the import uses `@vercel/analytics/next` for optimal integration
- The existing code structure and styling were preserved

### Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel, the analytics will automatically start tracking:
- Page views
- User interactions
- Performance metrics

The analytics data will be visible in the Vercel dashboard after the first users visit the deployed application.
